<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,959,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<treatmentCitationGroup infered="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
<taxonomicName authority="Regimbart, 1895: 43" authorityName="Regimbart" authorityPageNumber="43" authorityYear="1895" box="[151,601,994,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Herophydrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis box="[151,375,994,1017]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Herophydrus vittatus</emphasis>
<treatmentCitation author="Regimbart" box="[381,601,994,1017]" page="43" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" year="1895">
<bibRefCitation author="Regimbart" box="[381,564,994,1017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Regimbart, M. (1895) Revision des Dytiscidae et Gyrinidae d'Afrique et Madagascar et iles voisines. Memoires de la Societe Entomologiques de Belgique, 4, 1 - 244." type="journal article" year="1895">Régimbart, 1895</bibRefCitation>
: 43
</treatmentCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" box="[871,969,994,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[871,969,994,1017]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Hygrotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" box="[1081,1179,994,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1081,1179,994,1017]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Hygrotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. str.) by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Villastrigo, A., Ribera, I., Manuel, M., Millan, A. &amp; Fery, H. (2017 b) A new classification of the tribe Hygrotini Portevin, 19 29 (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae: Hydroporinae). Zootaxa, 4317 (3), 499 - 529." type="journal article">
Villastrigo 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">et al</emphasis>
. (2017b)
</bibRefCitation>
. Thus, this name became a junior secondary homonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sharp 1884: 441)" authorityName="Sharp" authorityPageNumber="441" authorityYear="1884" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus" subGenus="Leptolambus">
<emphasis box="[932,1030,1029,1052]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Hygrotus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1049,1187,1029,1052]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Leptolambus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1205,1283,1029,1052]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">vittatus</emphasis>
(
<treatmentCitation author="Sharp" page="441" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" year="1884">
<bibRefCitation author="Sharp" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Sharp, D. (1884) The water beetles of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, 1884, 439 - 464." type="journal article" year="1884">Sharp 1884: 441</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which was originally published in the binomen 
<taxonomicName box="[720,924,1064,1087]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Coelambus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis box="[720,924,1064,1087]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Coelambus vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter name was treated as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sharp, 1882)" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1882" baseAuthorityName="Sharp" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[186,730,1098,1121]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chinensis" subGenus="Leptolambus">
<emphasis box="[186,284,1098,1121]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Hygrotus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[306,444,1098,1121]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Leptolambus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[466,565,1098,1121]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">chinensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sharp" box="[585,724,1098,1121]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Sharp, D. (1882) On aquatic carnivorous Coleoptera or Dytiscidae. Scientific Transactions of the Royal Dublin Society, Series 2, 2, 179 - 1003 + pls. 7 - 18." type="journal article" year="1882">Sharp, 1882</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Balfour-Browne" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Balfour-Browne, J. (1947) The aquatic Coleoptera of Manchuria (Weymarn collection). The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 11, 13 (1946), 433 - 460." type="journal article" year="1947">
J. Balfour-Browne (1947: 438; with the subgeneric name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1860" box="[151,271,1133,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Coelambus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,271,1133,1156]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Coelambus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</bibRefCitation>
for the first time. Afterwards, however, the taxon was again interpreted as valid (e.g. by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk" box="[1252,1428,1133,1156]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. (2001) Dytiscidae. In: Tsalolikhin, S. J. (Ed.), Key to the freshwater invertebrates of Russia and adjacent lands, 5, pp. 1 - 836. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2001">Kirejtshuk 2001</bibRefCitation>
) until the synonymy was re-established by 
<treatmentCitation author="Fery" box="[599,782,1168,1191]" page="148" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" year="2003">
<bibRefCitation author="Fery" box="[599,782,1168,1191]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Fery, H. (2003) Dytiscidae: V. Taxonomic and distributional notes on Hygrotus Stephens, with emphasis on the Chinese fauna and a key to the Palearctic species (Coleoptera). In: Jach, M. A. &amp; Ji, L. (Eds.), Water Beetles of China. Vol. 3. Zoologisch-Botanische Gesellschaft in Osterreich and Wiener Coleopterologenverein, Wien, pp. 133 - 193." type="book" year="2003">Fery (2003: 148)</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,959,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">
Since no synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Regimbart" authorityName="Regimbart" box="[437,636,1206,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Coelambus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis box="[437,515,1206,1229]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">vittatus</emphasis>
Régimbart
</taxonomicName>
exists, the name must be substituted by a new replacement name. This is why I hereby substitute the invalid name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Regimbart, 1895)" authorityName="Regimbart" authorityYear="1895" baseAuthorityName="Regimbart" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[613,1095,1240,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis box="[613,711,1240,1263]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Hygrotus</emphasis>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[807,885,1240,1263]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">vittatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Regimbart" box="[902,1087,1240,1263]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" refString="Regimbart, M. (1895) Revision des Dytiscidae et Gyrinidae d'Afrique et Madagascar et iles voisines. Memoires de la Societe Entomologiques de Belgique, 4, 1 - 244." type="journal article" year="1895">Régimbart, 1895</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by the new replacement name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fery" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,249,1275,1298]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hygrotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="426" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,249,1275,1298]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">Hygrotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(s. str.) 
<emphasis box="[341,436,1275,1298]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">mauricei</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[445,558,1275,1299]" pageId="1" pageNumber="426">nom. nov.</emphasis>
The name is a substantive in the singular genitive formed from the forename of Maurice Régimbart and in honour of that great entomologist.
</paragraph>
